Project Plan

0.1 (Basics)
*   Decide on file format. SAX/DOM decision. DOM!
*   File format versioning support - future requirement.
*   Support scrolling map.
*   Support terrain palette.
*   Support named places.
*   Display labels for places.
*   Edit place info.
*   Try and use PNG format graphics.
*   Move source files into package directories.
*   Fix bugs in cursor position.
*   Produce correct headers/id for new/saved maps.

0.2 (Basics extra)
*   Support of named areas (setting tiles only).
*   Resize boundaries of a map (cmd line).
*   Hex overlay of map.
*   Hills support.
*   Faster display - precrop tile display etc.
*   Toolbar support for brush types.
*   Support square tiles for indoor maps.
*   Support printing to image file. (0.3)
*   Support for multiple display resolutions. (0.3)
*   Brush size options. (0.8)
*   File load/save inferface. (0.6)
*   Toolbar for common features. (0.6)
*   Wrapper class to provide GUI framework. (0.6)

0.2.1
*   Full world maps (inc 2D sphere support) (0.5).
*   Output to xplanet texture format (0.5).
*   Decouple sites from tiles.
*   Control over font used with sites.
*   Resize of site labels depending on tile size.
*   Consistency in naming. Sites = things, hills = features. Always.
*   Map creation dialogs.

0.2.2
*   Support rivers as vectors, inc graphical editing.
*   Support roads as vectors, inc graphical editing.
*   Properties on sites.
*   Rotation for tiles and features.
*   Rotation for Things (0.4).
*   Oversized Things (0.4).
*   Rotation on hexagonal maps as well as square maps.
*   Move <thing>/<river> tags into <tileset> ready for multi-tileset support.

0.2.3
    Support GUI map cropping and linking to submaps.
    Support GUI rescale facility (up and down).
    Make Tile class have package scope. Only TileSet should reference it directly.
*   Crop to highlighted regions (requires highlight support).
*   Crop to named area.
    Crop to things.
    Crop to rivers and roads.

0.2.4
    Fix display issues with area editing.
    Fix display issues with site editing.
    Feedback in a status bar to say what editing.

0.3 (Printing/XSLT support)
*   XSLT plugin for calling map from Yagsbook.
    Interface to pull out areas around named sites.
*   Support map cropping on image print.
    Create image from the GUI.

0.3.1
    Show A3/A4 crop areas on map as grid.
    Orientation and style of map labels.
    Auto-print overlapped image tiles to A3/A4 size.

0.4 (Finish standard features)
    Edit and set river properties, including name.
    Names for rivers and roads displayed on map.
    Creating/editing areas in GUI.
    Font styles for site labels.

0.4.1
    GUI for Merging child maps back into parent.

0.4.2
    Height palette. 2D display only.
    Contours.
    Fancy coastlines.
    Longitude/latitude calculation.
    Should be able to support full Harn map.

0.5 (Multiple tilesets)
    Fix low level support for multiple tilesets.
    Multiple floors for indoor maps.
    Transparent overlay of floors over each other.
    Calculation of connecting stairs between floors.

0.6 (UI design considerations)
    Map properties dialog/editor.
    Drop down palette menus from toolbar.
    Create world maps from the GUI.

0.7 (Web support)
    Output of web image maps (hrefs to places only).
    Wrap all resources into map bundle (jar?) for export.
    Applet viewer.

0.8 (Helper)
    Anti-aliase on rescale.
    Diff support for scaled children.
    Fill option.

0.9 (Optimisation)
    Any necessary speed enhancements.
    Any necessary memory efficiency enhancements.

1.0 (Release)
    Stability fixes.
    Run from jar file.
    Preferences file etc.
    Schema for file format.
    Documentation.

1.x (Wish list)
    href linking to documents on areas/places.
    3D display of terrain areas (isometric).
    3D display of terrain areas (perspective).
    Autogeneration of small area maps (villages etc).
    Undo support.
    Auto river generation.
    Editing terrain/place types.
    Variable coast masks for nicer display.
    Links into yagsbook for inline display of maps.
    Output SVG
    Random village names? Based on dictionary.

